<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Inches-to-Metric Conversion" class="currentChild" href="Inches-to-Metric_Conversion">Inches-to-Metric Conversion</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A conversion factor used to convert units of length expressed in the English system (i.e., inches) to a metric measurement (i.e., centimeters), as 1 inch equals 2.54 centimeters. Thus, to convert to centimeters, the number of inches is multiplied by 2.54 (i.e., a length that is 5 inches long would be converted as 5 x 2.54 = 12.7 centimeters). To convert to millimeters, the number of inches is multiplied by 25.4 (as there are 10 millimeters in a centimeter, and 25.4 millimeters in an inch). Thus, a 5-inch length would be converted as 5 x 25.4 = 127 millimeters. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
To convert from metric to inches, the number of inches in one centimeter can be used. (See <a title="Metric-to-Inches Conversion" href="Metric-to-Inches_Conversion">Metric-to-Inches Conversion</a>.) 
</p>
